# Phase 2 / Slice 5 — Report card materialization + Puppeteer PDF

Slice 4 closed (cp1 pure ranking + cp2 service/endpoints/gradebook). Slice 5
is the HEADLINE-RISK slice: Puppeteer at fly.io's memory budget, R2, BullMQ
render worker, the 40-card batch gate. Plan-first; plan approved, with THREE
of my leans OVERRIDDEN by my own pushback (the user accepted the pushbacks).

## Big de-risk: primitives already exist
R2 storage (StorageService.put/signUrl/delete, filesystem driver in dev / R2
in prod), BullMQ + tenantWorker, and the @Processor/@InjectQueue pattern all
shipped in Phase 1 (CSV import). StorageObjectKey is a typed union → slice 5
ADDS a `report-card` kind + a pathFor() entry. Workers run IN the API Nest
process (the imports precedent) — central to Q3.

## Settled decisions (3 pushbacks accepted)
- **Q3 worker process: IN-PROCESS, module-structured.** ReportCardRenderModule
  isolates the render processor. Mandated controls = pooled single browser +
  concurrency 1 + hard page timeout + page recycling. The 40-card memory gate
  (cp2) is the DATA-DRIVEN escalation trigger; if it fails → deferred
  external-service fallback OR a (then-contained) process split. BANKED LESSON:
  "when the spec says 'consider X', the considered escalation is the deferred
  entry, not the cp2 build." (Overrode my own (b)-separate lean.)
- **Q7 template: HAND-ROLLED TYPED TEMPLATE + mandatory esc().**
  renderReportCardHtml(data): string via template literals + array.map().join.
  esc() on every user-controlled field (names, comments, school name). cp2 (or
  a cp1 placeholder) unit-tests esc() against HTML-injection vectors (&,<,>,",',
  + a sample XSS payload). NO react/react-dom in the API runtime. BANKED:
  explicit escaping > implicit-by-framework for security-critical templates.
  (Overrode my own React lean.)
- **Q1b build calls aggregate: expose aggregateArmInTx(db, termId, classArmId).**
  Slice-4's aggregate() wraps its own withTenant for direct callers; the new
  public aggregateArmInTx takes an existing tx handle (delegates to the existing
  private runFullArmPass). Build calls it inside its own withTenant → atomic, no
  nested-tx deadlock. Small touch to slice-4 code (like slice-2 cp3 touched
  slice-1 for the freeze guard). BANKED: services composable inside other
  services' txs should expose *InTx variants.
- **Q1a build trigger: explicit POST /report-cards/arm/build.**
- **Q2 per-card jobs. Q4 concurrency 1. Q5 BullMQ auto-retry (attempts 3,
  exponential). Q6 R2 TTL 1h + overwrite same path on re-render.**
- **Q8 cp split = Option C (three cps):** cp1 = model + migration + RLS + build
  service + endpoints (build, board-feed, GET :id) + integration spec, NO PDF.
  cp2 = render worker (ReportCardRenderModule, pooled browser, conc 1, hard
  timeout, recycling) + Puppeteer + R2 (new key kind) + per-card render + POST
  /report-cards/arm/render + GET /:id/pdf + 40-CARD MEMORY GATE + manual smoke.
  cp3 = UI (board read view + Download PDF + Regenerate).

